    "AI systems are adaptable and allow learning materials to be tailored to individual needs, thereby enhancing student autonomy, and enabling early interventions for disengaged students (Algabri et al., 2021; Alotaibi & Alshehri, 2023; Bearman et al., 2023).",
    "Other significant benefits include the positive influence on learning outcomes, reduced administrative time for educators, and greater insight into student understanding.",
    "AI not only enhances traditional academic outcomes but also aids in professional training and specific skill development (Buchanan et al., 2021; Hwang et al., 2022; Sapci & Sapci, 2020).",
    "However, the adoption of AI in higher education is not without challenges.",
    "The most frequently cited concern is the lack of ethical consideration in AI applications, followed by issues related to curriculum development and infrastructure."
